The paper deals with image classification and localization tasks using a novel architecture that combines feature maps to locate class instances in an image. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a biologically inspired model that is free of differential connections and doesn't require separate training, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions using class activation for image classification, which could be related to natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
